Description:
 mx-updater - tray applet to notify of system and application updates
Changes:
 mx-updater (26.05.01mx25+dev01) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium
 .
   * Unify icon set definitions: updater-systray now uses updater_config
     as its sole source, thereby removing the duplicate hard-coded block.
   * Add support for admin-defined icon sets via
     /usr/local/etc/mx-updater.conf (priority) or /etc/mx-updater.conf.
     Up to 4 custom icon sets can be defined; replaces built-in sets when
     present. Falls back through locations and to built-ins on any error.
   * Settings editor: hide wireframe-transparent toggle when admin icon
     sets are active; disable icon selection when only one set is defined.
   * Sync disk, GUI and systray on load: invalid stored icon preference is
     corrected and written back immediately rather than silently ignored.
